<div id="review_559136211" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/559136211" />
    <a title="Johara " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4184297-johara"><img alt="Johara " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642736412p2/4184297.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/559136211?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Johara " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Johara " href="/user/show/4184297-johara">Johara </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/56293649-born-under-a-million-shadows">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer559136211" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17956245151876452340">Compared to the work of Khaled Hosseini, since the story takes place in Afghanistan, this book is different.. a forbidden love between an Englishwoman and an Afghani warlord, seen through the eyes of her young Afghani housekeeper.<br/><br/>Beautifully narrated, with interesting characters. I will not say it&apos;s the same work of Hosseini, as it&apos;s far from being on the same par as his books... but it&apos;s a decent attempt.</span>
  <span id="freeText17956245151876452340" style="display:none">Compared to the work of Khaled Hosseini, since the story takes place in Afghanistan, this book is different.. a forbidden love between an Englishwoman and an Afghani warlord, seen through the eyes of her young Afghani housekeeper.<br /><br />Beautifully narrated, with interesting characters. I will not say it's the same work of Hosseini, as it's far from being on the same par as his books... but it's a decent attempt.</span>
