<span id="freeTextContainer7050779470909862091">A beautifully written story about the life of a young boy growing up in Afghanistan after the fall of the Taliban. The title...a million shadows...describes perfectly how the Taliban has affected the life of the people there. <br/> <br/>Andrea Busfield&apos;s writing is beautiful, amazingly descriptive. She makes you feel comfortable and a part of the country and the people there. She makes you smile as you follow Fawad and his understanding of the world around him. She creates a deep sadness within you as you</span>
  <span id="freeText7050779470909862091" style="display:none">A beautifully written story about the life of a young boy growing up in Afghanistan after the fall of the Taliban. The title...a million shadows...describes perfectly how the Taliban has affected the life of the people there. <br /> <br />Andrea Busfield's writing is beautiful, amazingly descriptive. She makes you feel comfortable and a part of the country and the people there. She makes you smile as you follow Fawad and his understanding of the world around him. She creates a deep sadness within you as you read about the difficult lives and senseless deaths of those those that lived under the Taliban's regime. You will experience a full gamut of emotions and you are drawn to turn page-after-page until you reach the end of the book. And then, you will want to read it again-to be sure you haven't missed a word. </span>
