<span id="freeTextContainer2554110006748096471">The story was interesting enough but I found the book’s purpose unclear. Often it felt more like non fiction with the aim of explaining life in Afghanistan rather than a story about particular characters‘ lives. Farwad was more precocious than engaging. Although the story was told from his perspective his actions drove the plot which I found annoying. I’m feeling quite uncharitable about this book. If you’ve never read anything about Afghanistan then this might be a low key and accessible place </span>
  <span id="freeText2554110006748096471" style="display:none">The story was interesting enough but I found the book’s purpose unclear. Often it felt more like non fiction with the aim of explaining life in Afghanistan rather than a story about particular characters‘ lives. Farwad was more precocious than engaging. Although the story was told from his perspective his actions drove the plot which I found annoying. I’m feeling quite uncharitable about this book. If you’ve never read anything about Afghanistan then this might be a low key and accessible place to start but if you have any understanding already you might find that it doesn’t present anything new.</span>
