<div id="review_2463940518" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2463940518" />
    <a title="Isratquazi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14136349-isratquazi"><img alt="Isratquazi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1355699740p2/14136349.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2463940518?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Isratquazi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Isratquazi" href="/user/show/14136349-isratquazi">Isratquazi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2463940518" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1921062028187974052">Honestly, the beginning of the book was just amazing. I felt as if I am walking through the streets of Afghanistan and the story is just so real. You read about this in the newspaper but this book sort of gives you the picture of how war leaves a country completely torn apart and how it snatches the childhood away from all these kids. Also, how little involvement people have in terms of political decision making. In general, it&apos;s a good book and it will make you realize how lucky you are but wha</span>
  <span id="freeText1921062028187974052" style="display:none">Honestly, the beginning of the book was just amazing. I felt as if I am walking through the streets of Afghanistan and the story is just so real. You read about this in the newspaper but this book sort of gives you the picture of how war leaves a country completely torn apart and how it snatches the childhood away from all these kids. Also, how little involvement people have in terms of political decision making. In general, it's a good book and it will make you realize how lucky you are but what i had the most problem was with the ending. The ending was just really quick, i felt Andrea just wanted to finish the story really quickly and dropped the ending all of a sudden. I think the ending deserved more explanation and maybe I am a sucker for a really good ending or some kind of ending, so to me it felt incomplete.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1921062028187974052" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


