<div id="review_103257797" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/103257797" />
    <a title="Shanna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3329818-shanna"><img alt="Shanna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1430432037p2/3329818.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/103257797?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shanna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shanna" href="/user/show/3329818-shanna">Shanna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3329818-shanna?shelf=andrea-busfield">andrea-busfield</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer103257797" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15012229094931672375">Loved this book!! Fawad is a sweet and inquisitive little boy who you just loving following page after page. He charms you right from the beginning as he experiences love,loss and life living in Afghanistan. The author shows you the everyday life of Afghan&apos;s and yet puts an interesting &quot;Western&quot; twist to it all which is done, I think, extremely well. Fawad will keep you entertained right to the end. A must read! </span>
  <span id="freeText15012229094931672375" style="display:none">Loved this book!! Fawad is a sweet and inquisitive little boy who you just loving following page after page. He charms you right from the beginning as he experiences love,loss and life living in Afghanistan. The author shows you the everyday life of Afghan's and yet puts an interesting "Western" twist to it all which is done, I think, extremely well. Fawad will keep you entertained right to the end. A must read! </span>
  <a data-text-id="15012229094931672375" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
